cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE, cs.CL

The paper focuses on analyzing Facebook Reactions to scholarly content, which involves social media and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
